entry.def: Teeth is the plural of tooth.

means.word_mean: 1. the kind and number and arrangement of teeth (collectively) in a person or animal

example.en: They dropped their teeth when I told them I was married.
example.zh: 我告诉他们我已结婚了，他们听了非常惊讶。

example.en: I do drop my teeth at the notion that Shakespeare is busted and needs to be fixed.
example.zh: 有人居然认为莎士比亚的作品写得不好，需要修改，我听了不禁大吃一惊。

list.explanation: 同意或答应干某事，(开始)认真处理、紧紧抓住某事

example.en: I can't wait to get my teeth into that Wallace job.
example.zh: 我想尽快接手华莱士干的那份差事。

example.en: Here. Sink your teeth into this and see if you can manage this project.
example.zh: 现在，开始好好十这事吧，者看你是否能够完成这个计划。

means.word_mean: 致力于( 有难度的事)；认真处理

sentences.en: This job is too easy. Why can’t they give me something I can really get my teeth into?
sentences.cn: 这活儿太容易了，为什么他们不能让我干点我真正需要费点劲的事情呢？

means.word_mean: (组织、法律等)强大有效；有杀伤力

sentences.en: It appears that the new legislation doesn’t have any teeth, since there has been no improvement in working conditions.
sentences.cn: 新法规似乎不太有效，因为人们的工作条件没什么改善。

sentences.en: The new law was passed in the teeth of strong opposition.
sentences.cn: 尽管遭到了强烈的反对，新法仍然得以通过。

sentences.en: They crossed the Atlantic in the teeth of a force 10 wind.
sentences.cn: 他们冒着10级大风穿越了大西洋。
